      "role": "user",
      "content": "exactly. and it's more than just proprietary signals. when i look at the frequency, it's too rhythmic, too deliberate. it's like the metadata is acting as a high-level ledger for value that never actually touches a bank account. it's almost like the value exists in the *relationship* between the data points rather than the numbers in the logs. if this were true, it would mean the \"real\" global economy is actually happening in the overhead of the internet, completely detached from the GDP we see in the news. how would a system like that even be regulated if the \"money\" is just specific arrangements of data?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
